==Finnish==
===Noun===

halvattu (genitive/intensifier ''halvatun'', illative ''halvattuun'', elative ''halvatusta'', inessive ''halvatussa'', partitive ''halvattua'')

(mediocre ''expletive'' or ''intensifier'') hell, fuck shit.

Finnish synonyms: [[helvetti]], [[hitto]], [[hiisi]], [[piru]]

===Examples===

* Plain: ''Kuka halvattu on puhkonut mun autoni renkaat?'' Who the hell has punctured my car tyres?
* Illative: ''Mihin halvattuun mä olen pudottanut avaimeni?'' Where the hell have I dropped my keys?
* Inessive: ''Missä halvatussa mun lmpakkoni on?'' Where the hell is my wallet?
* Elative: ''Mistä halvatusta toi tyyppi ilmaantui?'' Where the hell did that guy come from?
* Intensifier: ''Se halvatun persläpi on syypää kaikkeen.'' That fucking asshole is the culprit for it all.
* Partitive: ''Mitä halvattua täällä tapahtuu?'' What the hell is going on here?

===Usage notes===

''Halvattu'' is seldom or never used as an object in an imperative sentence. See ''[[hitto]]'' for explanation.

===Etymology===

Halvattu is a corrupt of [[helvetti]] and it sounds much like ''halvaantunut'', [[paralyze]]d. This can have a connection to old religious beliefs that disablilities are punishments for sin.